The paper discusses the channel hardening phenomenon in MIMO communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The physical channel model used in the paper also suggests a possible connection to systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper highlights the influences of propagation rays and antenna array topologies, which could be relevant to physics (cs.PHYS).
